unc
------------------------------------------
UNC is a lightweight and simple unicode library.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.6.10-1
  libgcc1-14.4.0-1
  libstdc++6-14.4.0-1
  libunc-devel-1.0+git20120507-1bl1
  libunc1-1.0+git20120507-1bl1
  pkg-config-2.5.1-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.46.1-1
  cmake-4.2.1-1
  cygport-0.37.7-1
  gcc-core-14.4.0-1
  gcc-g++-14.4.0-1
  ninja-1.13.2-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/udoprog/unc

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/udoprog/unc.git

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack unc-1.0+git20120507-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./unc-1.0+git20120507-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/unc-1.0+git20120507-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/unc-1.0+git20120507-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libunc1-1.0+git20120507-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libunc-devel-1.0+git20120507-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(unc)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/unc.README
  /usr/share/doc/unc/README.md

(libunc1)
  /usr/bin/cygunc-1.dll
  /usr/bin/cyguncdata-1.dll

(libunc-devel)
  /usr/include/unc/iso8859.hpp
  /usr/include/unc/unc.hpp
  /usr/include/unc/unccase.hpp
  /usr/lib/libunc.dll.a
  /usr/lib/libuncdata.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/unc.pc

------------------

